2. Moved the fillna(0) call back to the exact spot it occurs in the original code (after dropping cols but before detecting cats/conts), so NaNs are handled identically.
Removed the dtype-preservation logic (which changed column types) and replaced the vectorized boolean cast with the original column-by-column approach to ensure identical dtypes.
